-s</i>.","Scottish: habitational name from Raffles in Mouswald (Dumfriesshire), comprising Old Norse <i>ref-hol</i> ‘fox-hole’ in a Scots plural form."]},{"name":"Reveal","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Revell  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":4,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705197,"age":77,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"John Revell was born in 1378, in Liversedge, Yorkshire, England. He married Mary Comberford in 1401, in Liversedge, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in England."},"et":{"1378–":"1378–Surnud","1381–Female":"1381–Surnud","1402–1490":"1402–1490","1378–Male":"1378–Surnud","1402":"1402","1401":"1401","1378":"1378","1455":"1455","1382":"1382","1381":"1381","1490":"1490","England":"England","Liversedge, Yorkshire, England":"Liversedge, Yorkshire, England","Birstall, Yorkshire, England":"Birstall, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1378–":"1378–Kuollut","1381–Female":"1381–Kuo